      • REQUIREMENT_BEANS_DIRECTIVE

        public static final java.lang.String REQUIREMENT_BEANS_DIRECTIVE
        The 'beans' directive on the CDI extender requirement.

        The value of this directive is a comma delimited list of bean class names that should be processed by the CDI container. When used, no other classes in the bundle should be instantiated as beans. This set of class names may be further reduced by exclusions in the beans.xml file.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • REQUIREMENT_REFERENCES_DIRECTIVE

        public static final java.lang.String REQUIREMENT_REFERENCES_DIRECTIVE
        The 'references' directive on the CDI extender requirement.

        The value of this directive is a comma delimited list of bean class names who's injection points should be satisfied by OSGi services.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • REQUIREMENT_SERVICES_DIRECTIVE

        public static final java.lang.String REQUIREMENT_SERVICES_DIRECTIVE
        The 'services' directive on the CDI extender requirement.

        The value of this directive is a comma delimited list of bean class names that should be published as OSGi services.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
